==Arabic==
===Alternative spellings===
انا، أَنَا: 'anā, ana (I)
ـني، ـنِي: -nī, ni (me)
ـي، ـِي، ـيَ: -ī, i (my)
===Etymology===
أَنَا from Proto-Semitic *'anāk-, ultimately Afro-Asiatic (with cognates in Berber nekk, Egyptian ink (Coptic anok), etc.)

===Pronunciation===
IPA: /ʔanaː/ [ʔɛnɛː]
/-niː/
/-iː/ (after long vowels /-ja/)
===Pronoun===
Subject pronoun.
#أَنَا [[I]].
#ـنِي [[me]].
#ـِي [[my]].
